<dl id="n36189c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36189c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36189c"> 189(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> stockade</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The land being thus fairly purchased of the Indians, a circumstance very unusual in the history of colonization, and strongly illustrative of the honesty of the Dutch progenitors, a <mark>stockade</mark> fort and trading-house were forthwith erected on an eminence in front of the place where the good St. Nicholas had appeared in a vision to Oloffe the Dreamer. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 58</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
